          <head/>
          <msContents>
            <summary>A work on Logic by the priest Buṭrus bin Buṭrus bin Isḥaq al-Tūlāti of Aleppo.
              The manuscript is not dated but Mingana puts the date of production around 1750 CE
              based on the handwriting.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
            <msItem xml:id="manuscript_14529_item_1">
              <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Kitāb al-Manṭiq</title>
              <title xml:lang="ar">كتاب المنطق</title>
              <author key="person_35591705"><persName>Buṭrus bin Buṭrus bin Isḥaq al-Tūlāti of
                  Aleppo</persName> (<persName>بطرس بن بطرس ابن اسحق التولاتي واعظ مدينة
                  حلب</persName>), likely the same as <persName>Tūlāwī, Buṭrus,
                1657-1745</persName></author>              
              <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
              <note><p>According to Mingana, the author is the same as Buṭrus al-Tūlāwi, a Maronite
                  priest who died in Aleppo in 1745. He ws educated in a Maronite school of Rome.
                  (Cf. <title>Catalogue Manuscrits Auteurs Arabes Chrétiens Depuis L'Islam</title>
                by Louis Cheikho (Bayrūt: Maṭbaʻat al-Ābāʼ al-Yasūʻīyīn
                1924), page. 76. </p>
                <p> The work is divided into eigtheen baḥths, subdivided into an unequal number of
                  faṣls.</p>
                <p><locus from="1b" to="4b">Folios 1b-4b</locus>: index.</p>
                <p><locus from="213a" to="216a">Folios 213a-216a</locus>: a definition of philosophical and theological
                  terms. Headed <quote xml:lang="ar">التعاريف الموجودة في هذا
                المجلد</quote></p></note>
              <incipit><locus from="5a">Folio 5a</locus>: البحث الاول في موضوع المنطق الفصل الاول في
                ماهة المنطق وتعريفه</incipit>
              <explicit>تم المنطق وابوابه والله اعلم تم</explicit>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
